race.comment: SCHEHERAZADE (8) resumes here but the form she showed when last in work was good enough for a race of this calibre. Tuned up for this with a recent trial placing and a strong showing while fresh is on the cards. LA PETITE MAISON (4) has hit the top-five in 11 of 12 career outings and doesn't know how to put in a poor one. Has to be included. CUTEPI (2) was a bit plain first-up but bounced back to form with a solid Ballina victory last time out. In the mix if she brings her A-game. STARSARISE (9) has been in the firing line in all three runs this campaign and it's hard to knock mares in form. Top-three aspirations. MISHANI CROWN (5) best of the rest with the 1.5kg claim.
